question: Saints vs. Jaguars
description:
In the upcoming NFL game, scheduled for October 19, 8:15 PM ET:

If the New Orleans Saints win, the market will resolve to “Saints”.

If the Jacksonville Jaguars win, the market will resolve to “Jaguars”.

 If the game is not completed by October 26, 2023 (11:59 PM ET) or it ends in a tie, the market will resolve 50-50.

question: Will AI be the 2023 TIME Person of the Year?
description:
If "AI", "Artificial Intelligence", or another phrase directly referring to artificial intelligence (e.g. ChatGPT, GPT-4) is named as TIME's Person of the Year for 2023, this market will resolve to "Yes". Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

Please note, that this market will resolve to "Yes" if AI is named TIME's Person of the Year either alone or in conjunction with another person or thing, so long as AI is directly referenced. If, for example, the Person of the Year is "AI and Sam Altman", this market will resolve to "Yes". If, however, the Person of the Year is the "OpenAI Team", this market will resolve to "No".

If Time's cover and other Time webpages have different winners for the Person of the Year, only one of them has to mention AI or AI models/interfaces as the winner for this market to resolve to "Yes".

This market can resolve after the 2023 TIME's Person of the Year is announced by TIME magazine. If for any reason the 2023 TIME's Person of the Year is not announced by January 15, 2024 (11:59 PM ET), this market will resolve to "No".

question: Will Biden visit Saudi Arabia in 2023?
description:
If U.S. President Biden visits Saudi Arabia between October 19 and December 31, 11:59 PM ET, this market will resolve to "Yes". Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

For the purpose of this market, a "visit" is defined as Biden physically entering the terrestrial or maritime territory of Saudi Arabia. Whether or not Biden enters Saudi airspace during the timeframe of this market will have no bearing on a positive resolution.

The primary resolution source for this information will be official information from government of the United States of America, official information from Biden or released by his verified social media accounts (e.g. https://twitter.com/POTUS), and official information from Saudi Arabia (e.g. https://twitter.com/ksamofaen); however, a consensus of credible reporting will also be used.

question: Will Sheikh Jassim buy Man United in 2023?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Sheikh Jassim agrees to acquires a controlling stake of Manchester United FC by December 31, 2023, 11:59:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No". This market will resolve immediately if any deal to acquire a controlling stake in Manchester United FC is reached, including other bidders.

For the purposes of this market a "controlling stake" is defined as at least 50% of Manchester United FC shares. 

The primary resolution source for this market will be official information from Manchester United FC as well as other official publicly-available information, however a consensus of credible reporting will also be used.

question: Will crude oil hit $120 in 2023?
description:
This is a market on whether the price of crude oil will be at $120.00 or higher at any point between October 11 and December 29, 2023 ET (inclusive). If the value of a barrel of oil reaches $120.00 or greater by market close on the resolution date, this market will resolve to “Yes”. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No". 

The resolution source for this market will be NASDAQ's reporting on the values offered by the New York Mercantile Exchange (NYMEX), found at https://www.nasdaq.com/market-activity/commodities/cl%3Anmx/historical. The resolution will be based on the values listed in the column labelled “High”.

question: Will Saudi Arabia boost oil production in Q4?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Saudi Arabia increases their level of crude oil production (in tb/d) in Q4 of 2023 over the level in Q3 of 2023. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

The resolution source for this market will be information released by OPEC based on direct communication, after the close of the 4th financial quarter for 2023 (e.g. https://www.opec.org/opec_web/en/publications/338.htm + https://www.opec.org/opec_web/static_files_project/media/downloads/publications/Addendum_October%20MOMR.pdf).

question: Will Salah join a Saudi club next transfer window?
description:
This is a market on whether Mohamed Salah, the current Liverpool player, will sign for any football club in the Saudi Pro League in the Winter transfer window, which closes on January 31, 2024.

This market will resolve to “Yes” if it is announced that Salah has signed for any team in the Saudi Pro League during the transfer window. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

This market will also resolve to “No” if it is announced that Salah has signed a contract extension with Liverpool or a new contract with any club not in the Saudi Pro League.

If a club announces that Salah has signed with them but later retracts that announcement, this market will resolve according to the initial announcement.

This market's resolution source will be official, credible announcements from either Liverpool or the signing club.
